a `TestCase(String name)` constructor.\n  - Covers fallback to a no-argument constructor.\n  - Asserts the suite creates exactly one `TestCase` and assigns the discovered test name.\n- Updated `tests/src/junit/junit/3.7/src/test/resources/META-INF/native-image/reachability-metadata.json`\n  - Added reflection metadata for the helper `TestCase` constructors and declared methods used by `TestSuite`.\n\nI did not compile or run tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_0ae16f0ab1b1b31b0169f96204b1e48191bdb798abddec34b5\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1026, "output": 1706, "cacheRead": 31232, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33964, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1777951215083, "responseId": "resp_0ae16f0ab1b1b31b0169f961ef8c2c8191951b6acc0787cbdd"}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering test cases and structure**\n\nI'm thinking about whether to include TestCase for allDeclaredMethods in the test resource. It might cover a broad library package, but should I focus on the active class only and its metadata? I want to avoid changing library metadata since it's not necessary. I'm wondering if a no-arg TestCase class in JUnit 4 can return a Test using createTest. This might be an option to directly call TestSuite.createTest instead of getting declared methods.\n\n**Clarifying Java assertions**\n\nI'm considering if there's a potential invalid file due to the unresolved `assertTrue(true)`. Since I'm dealing with nested class extensions of TestCase, the inherited static method can be called directly from instance methods. TestCase extends Assert, and assertTrue being static in Assert means Java should allow static calls this way. After some reflection, I think it should be fine to call the inherited static method by its simple name.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0ae16f0ab1b1b31b0169f961f0441881919fd65b8a9a20bd43\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-WIEoV73_lrkmj3gF0OvGC3QHl8GC1f_jqnjFzZsf8je5UrOH_kosF2Sr8mzAjFBNSAALW-GQ_asN1S296DDX38AIq9YRnEcpwjW7bh19XAsAhNZLigrzm_C80kJB9vc6HAJ3Fi_eybmAt7Ph0wGO3Xq9PedlMT065pbQ4ptV2MDtu5qeX5-ODBzAac68zCSBF9LNw9Q409M58AmzNa5UGKgqQhzMBfm5be2lpNUzYAFcVdNYoEtn-1oJh2-Wo-3lRdTDJpf_8-y0YFHucqUF3sHfNpPD6H06rqUQ8LYwyoRwx1EBdeWEujidWZ6N3gvEcq5DCXNj8wBYld96VvTETnUvl9qbzggMxEF0PHNE2KXDsTgkmPn3fdFUT_tfU6x3XcQxxgw9a1sF934T--04LDIRB3Wfo7-vchDBQaHzC1Nhs9Kl_sr85tMFM7XSMCrdcp6_miH-67olN-kO3jHfwweIbJh2Nk8ICckaGivS1bTFwTjMOyoIG79JhoqmY5oiZqMt-8MGyPjy_pLCupVSqudo4APsqSDc8mCPcKJ-VN7xOmR8eAfTUfmpA6VaZqiZ1_WeNSDNiny5wrpHwHRQYdpljMh2aq-HocD_0EN2v1CjWes6vXFAouoYUk4efEVlvBH2nCUnejiRm5-FyMItCzzmq98qMYmsag6GTUd_QklU1HrRYeZpWOJ8D4LgFzv0NT677K5oPQdMCHyyVUXKMNE0_M_U_VbBVcKi25l7V01IhucCwoAg4_4ZqQf9Oto0RnzUnE